----------------------------------------------------------------
Font Artifact License Addendum
Version 1.0
----------------------------------------------------------------

This Addendum applies to generated font artifacts and derived font products.
This Addendum does not change the MIT License terms above for the Software
itself.

1. Definitions

- "Artifacts" means images, glyph samples, intermediates, or other generated
  outputs produced by running the Software.
- "Font Product" means any distributed font file, font package, or font family
  containing one or more glyphs created in whole or in part from Artifacts.
- "Attributed Character Count" means the number of unique characters (for
  example, unique Unicode code points) in a distributed Font Product that were
  created in whole or in part from Artifacts.

2. Permissions

Subject to this Addendum, you may use, copy, modify, distribute, sublicense,
and sell Artifacts and Font Products for commercial or non-commercial purposes.

3. Attribution Trigger (More Than 200 Characters)

If you distribute a Font Product with an Attributed Character Count greater
than 200, you must provide attribution that includes:

- the statement: "Created using zi2zi-JiT artifacts"
- a link to this repository:
  https://github.com/kaonashi-tyc/zi2zi-JiT

Attribution may appear in documentation, a README, an about page, package
metadata, marketplace listing, or another reasonably visible location that is
distributed with or alongside the Font Product.

For Font Products with an Attributed Character Count of 200 or fewer,
attribution is not required by this Addendum.

4. No Trademark License

This Addendum does not grant any right to use names, logos, or trademarks of
the licensors except as required for the attribution text in Section 3.

5. Warranty and Liability

Artifacts and Font Products are provided "AS IS", without warranty of any kind,
express or implied, including but not limited to merchantability, fitness for a
particular purpose, and non-infringement. In no event shall the licensors be
liable for any claim, damages, or other liability, whether in contract, tort,
or otherwise, arising from or in connection with Artifacts or Font Products.
